House Resolution 890
By: Representatives Holcomb of the 101st, Miller of the 62nd, and Evans of the 57th
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Hope Atlanta on 125 years of service to metro Atlanta; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Hope Atlanta was founded in 1900 as Travelers Aid Atlanta to assist vulnerable
3 individuals arriving in the city and to provide essential guidance, shelter, and reunification
4 services; and
5 WHEREAS, Travelers Aid Atlanta was renamed Hope Atlanta in 2009, and it has served
6 hundreds of thousands of people since its founding; and
7 WHEREAS, throughout its 125-year history, Hope Atlanta has evolved to meet the needs of
8 metro Atlanta's most vulnerable populations, including veterans, families, and individuals
9 experiencing homelessness; and
10 WHEREAS, Hope Atlanta provided support to service members and their families during
11 World War I and World War II; and
12 WHEREAS, Hope Atlanta has been a leader in disaster relief, offering critical aid to
13 displaced individuals following significant events such as Hurricane Katrina, the 1996
14 Olympic Games, and the COVID-19 pandemic; and
